@startuml freegen
!include ../_includes/style.iuml

title Free-gen probe — slice 7c (« sonder la teuté du modèle »)

state "Tree characterization\nfinished (slice 4c)" as TREE_DONE
state "characterizeTree.ts\n  if (opts.embed) {…}" as GATE
state "freegen.runFreeGenProbe()" as PROBE {
  state "1× model call\nFREEGEN_PROMPT\n(topic-neutral,\n~600–800 words)" as ASK
  state "Strip <think>…</think>\n(D11)" as STRIP
  state "1× embed call\n(query text)" as EMB
  state "Project onto 32\nleaf anchors\n(probe-anchors.json)" as PROJECT
  state "Reduce to\n• topic_coverage_per_leaf\n• topic_coverage_per_branch\n• freegen_words\n• freegen_excerpt" as REDUCE
}
state "merge into signature\n(`scoring_scheme` unchanged)" as MERGE
state "skip silently\n(no embedder configured)" as SKIP_S
state "log + skip\n(probe failure isolated)" as SKIP_E

TREE_DONE --> GATE
GATE --> PROBE : embed seam present
GATE --> SKIP_S : opts.embed absent\n(SPEC §4 strict path)

PROBE --> ASK
ASK --> STRIP
STRIP --> EMB
EMB --> PROJECT
PROJECT --> REDUCE
REDUCE --> MERGE

PROBE --> SKIP_E : ANY throw\n(embedder down, empty\nresponse, refusal…)

note right of MERGE
  Fields are **additional
  evidence** in routing
  (α=0.7 deterministic,
  β=0.3 coverage blend).
  Never replace `scores_per_leaf`.
end note

note bottom of SKIP_E
  DECISIONS.md DCC §5 —
  probe failure NEVER sinks
  the tree pass that already
  computed scores_per_leaf.
end note

@enduml
